parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.

and there may be a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the speedometer to shut off, the odometer to stop clocking miles, the ABS system to shut down, and the traction control system to shut off, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The dashboard lights up with multiple warnings
and check engine lights; speedometer and odometer cease to operate; intermittent or permanent loss of ABS and traction control systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Disconnection and Fuel Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disconnection of the fuel line from the pump can cause fuel leakage, leading to a loss of power, engine stalling, and potentially a fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Ignition Cassette and Fuel Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition cassette and fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
A poorly designed catalytic converter can cause a noxious smell, potentially irritating the lungs and causing discomfort.
A loud noise coming from the gas tank can be a nuisance and potentially indicate a more serious issue.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the gas tank as gas moves in the tank.
